Reasoning: The paper deals with graph games with {\omega}-regular winning conditions, which are commonly used in the analysis of reactive systems and programs. This falls under the category of logic in computer science (cs.LO). The paper also discusses set-based symbolic algorithms, which are used for the analysis of large finite-state systems, and thus could be categorized under data structures (cs.DS) and computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also mentions program repair and verification of branching time properties, which could fall under programming languages (cs.PL) and formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL).
